Unlike the DS scene, where the best available emulator is the apparently abandoned freeware version of NO$GBA, the NES scene has very high quality <a href="http://www.fsf.org/licensing/essays/free-sw.html" class="postlink">Free</a> emulators such as Nintendulator, Nestopia, and FCEU*. So yes, it would be possible to hack a new mapper into a decent emu.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Sep 05, 2008 8:19 am</p><hr />
